titleproper.value: Guide to the Papers of Frances Patai <num>ALBA.131</num>

author.value: Collection processed by Angela Frattarola and Ted Casselman

publisher.value: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives

addressline: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archive

creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace
        <date>2017-08-15T19:22:20</date>

corpname.value: Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives

abstract.value:
Frances Patai was an educator, writer,
        historian and feminist activist. Born in New York in 1930 she earned her bachelors and
        masters degrees at the City College of New York in the 1950s and taught English and
        communication courses throughout the City University of New York (CUNY) system. Throughout
        her career Patai was concerned with the rights and status of women, and in the last decade
        of her life she devoted her efforts to researching and writing a book on women medical
        personnel who volunteered during the Spanish Civil War. Patai died in 1998 before she could
        bring her project to fruition. She was 67 years old. The Patai Papers consist predominantly
        of research materials she gathered and drafts she produced during the course of her work on
        her unpublished book, <title render="italic">Heroines of the Good Fight: U.S. Women
          Volunteers in the Spanish Civil War</title>including articles, clippings, and
        notes.

p.value:
Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Tamiment Library & Robert F.
        Wagner Labor Archives for more information and to schedule an appointment,
        tamiment.wagner@nyu.edu or 212-998-2630.

Published citations should take the following form: <lb/><lb/>Identification of item, date;
        Collection name; Collection number; box number; folder number; <lb/>Tamiment Library/Robert
        F. Wagner Labor Archives <lb/>Elmer Holmes Bobst Library <lb/>70 Washington Square South
        <lb/>New York, NY 10012, New York University Libraries.

<list>
          <item>Rimmel, Leslie, "Frances (Francesca) Patai, 1930-1998," <title render="italic">Off
              Our Backs</title>(Washington), April 1998.</item>
          <item>Leberstein, Stephen, "Eloquence of Former Chancellor Sparks Major CCNY Bequest,"
              <title render="italic">CUNY Matters</title>, Spring 1998.</item>
        </list>

Series III: This series is made up of subject files. Included here are notes, excerpt from
        publications, and research materials on general topics, organizations, and individuals as
        well as biographical material on Patai. Notable among these files are copies of Jirku
        Gusti's, "We Fight Death," and Sandor Voros' unpublished manuscript on hospitals and medical
        services.
